result.execSummary:
The defendant Jason R. Bauknecht was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Delivered to LCSD
Mailed to def. 10-06-2017
On def's failure to pay the fine, Court orders 26 days jail.

Defendant Jason R. Bauknecht in court with attorney Brent Harold Debord.  Defendant Jason R. Bauknecht in custody.  Elizabeth R. Constable appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 13CF222, 14CF131 and 16CM143 @ 10:10 a.m. 13CF222 ct 1 and 14CF131 ct 1 & 2 sentencing after revocation -  parties have received revocation packets. No additions or corrections. State joins in Dept's recommendation of 1 yr jail on each ct, concurrent. Will stipulate to sentence credit provided by Atty Debord. Response by Atty Debord. Agrees with Dept's recommendation. Credit for 191 days on 13CF222 and 175 days on 14CF131. Requests huber. Statement by Defendant. Remarks by the Court. 13CF222 Court orders 1 yr jail, credit for 191 days, huber, covert any outstanding obligations to civil judgment. Def advised of firearms and voting restrictions. 14CF131 ct 1 - 1 yr jail, concurrent to 13CF222, credit for 175 days served, huber. Ct 2 - 1 yr jail, credit for 175 days served, concurrent. All outstanding court obligations converted to civil judgment. Postconviction rights. 16CM143 - agreement stated: State moves to amend to DC w/out enhancer, 30 days jail consecutive to any other sentence, court costs. Atty Debord and Def agree. Plea quest. reviewed. Court grants motion to amend to disorderly conduct 947.01. No contest plea. Constitutional rights, elements, possible penalties reviewed. Atty Debord satisfied. Court finds Def understands and plea freely & voluntarily made. Factual basis found. Court accepts plea and finds guilty of disorderly conduct. Counsel ask Court to accept joint recommendation. Nothing by Defendant. Remarks by the Court. Will follow agreement. 30 days jail, huber. Court costs. DNA surcharge and sample. No credit for time served. Postconviction rights. Pmt plan. State has complied with victim rights. (Clarified w/Judge 30 days is consecutive to other sentences)

Defendant Jason R. Bauknecht in court via videowith attorney Brent Harold Debord.  Defendant Jason R. Bauknecht in custody.  Galen Bayne-Allison appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Complaint received, reviewed and waive reading.  Not guilty plea entered.  Reserve jurisdictional objections.  Court will received plea.  Bond will continue.  Def is on probation hold  Status conference scheduled for September 12, 2016 at 03:30 pm.

Defendant Jason R. Bauknecht in court via video, in custody.  Galen Bayne-Allison appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called @ 1:42 p.m. Court reviews status. Warrant was authorized yesterday, however, Def was still in custody. Statement by Defendant. Court vacates warrant.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for July 25, 2016 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Jason R. Bauknecht not in court.  Galen Bayne-Allison appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Called at 4:13 pm.  Court reviews court record.  State request warrant, $500. or body only.  Adjacent counties.  Court orders warrant $1000.00 or body, Langlade and adjacent counties
